<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1901-06-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1901-06-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="509" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d509">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Russell</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Caracas</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-06-15"><hi rend="italic">June 15,
                                1901.</hi></date></dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 629.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inform you that on the
                            9th instant a cable was received by the President of Venezuela from the
                            governor of the island of Margarita, notifying him that an American
                            man-of-war (presumably the <hi rend="italic">Mayflower</hi>) was
                            anchored off the port of Juan Griego, but had not entered.</p>
                        <p>The President has cabled for details regarding the arrival and anchorage
                            of the <hi rend="italic">Mayflower.</hi></p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">William W.
                            Russell.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>